orum.xda-developers.com/xperia-xa/review/contrast-true-blacks-t3642759"], "threads": []}, {"title": "Color saturation & accuracy", "rating": 3.0, "links": ["https://forum.xda-developers.com/xperia-xa/review/color-saturation-accuracy-t3642760"], "threads": []}, {"title": "Clarity/resolution", "rating": 4.0, "links": ["https://forum.xda-developers.com/xperia-xa/review/clarity-resolution-t3642761"], "threads": []}, {"title": "Minimum brightness", "rating": 5.0, "links": ["https://forum.xda-developers.com/xperia-xa/review/minimum-brightness-t3642762"], "threads": []}, {"title": "Call quality", "rating": 4.5, "links": ["https://forum.xda-developers.com/xperia-xa/review/call-quality-t3642763"], "threads": []}, {"title": "WiFi strength, range, and throughput", "rating": 4.0, "links": ["https://forum.xda-developers.com/xperia-xa/review/wifi-strength-range-throughput-t3642764"], "threads": [{"text": "Just started with this phone, coming from Z1c, and I'm impressed with the WiFi signal strength. It's been my biggest gripe with new phones in general, (why is my SE w995 from 2009 the only phone I can find that connects in this room?)... Seems like they finally got around to addressing it. This phone is right up there with my w995", "time": "26th July 2017, 03:39 AM", "postID": "post73174360", "replies": []}]}, {"title": "Cellular strength and throughput", "rating": 3.5, "links": ["https://forum.xda-developers.com/xperia-xa/review/cellular-strength-throughput-t3642765"], "threads": [{"text": "Not as strong a signal as some of my other Mediatek devices.\r\n3 uk 7.0 FW installed but I still need to use the Three WiFi app indoors to make calls, send and receive sms messages", "time": "4th October 2017, 07:34 PM", "postID": "post74036491", "replies": []}]}, {"title": "Speakerphone (loudness, clarity)", "rating": 5.0, "links": ["https://forum.xda-developers.com/xperia-xa/review/speakerphone-loudness-clarity-t3642766"], "threads": []}]